    "He died of cancer at age 83.": [],
    "His students included <a href=\"/landaus&gt;Sarah Landau&lt;/a&gt; and&lt;a data-cke-saved-href=\">Vincent Scully, Jr.</a>, [the latter at Yale, though he did not have a permanent appointment there].": [],
    "Hitchcock was a founding member of the Victorian Society and a former president of the Victorian Society of America.": [],
    "His books on Victorian architecture helped to rehabilitate a neglected field.": [],
    "As an architectural historian, he remained noticeable apart from the debates of post-modernism.": [],
    "David Watkin termed Hitchcock's scholarly work \"thorough and workman-like though lacking in the kind of conceptual or intellectual interest which characterizes the work of German-inspired art historians.\"": [
